## Multi-Workspace Group Configuration

Your bundle is configured for **separate workspaces per environment**. Groups must exist in **every workspace** where targets will deploy.

### Account-Level vs Workspace-Level Groups

Databricks supports two types of groups:
- **Account-level groups** (recommended): Created in the [Databricks Account Console](https://accounts.cloud.databricks.com). Can be assigned to multiple workspaces.
- **Workspace-level groups** (legacy): Created within a single workspace. Cannot be shared across workspaces.

### Recommended Setup

1. **Create groups at the account level** via the Account Console or [SCIM provisioning](https://docs.databricks.com/aws/en/admin/users-groups/scim/)
2. **Assign groups to each workspace** where targets will deploy:
{{- if eq .include_dev_environment "yes" }}
  - Dev workspace: `developers`, `analytics_team`
{{- end }}
  - Stage workspace: `developers`, `qa_team`, `analytics_team`
{{- if eq .environment_setup "full" }}
  - Prod workspace: `operations_team`, `analytics_team`
{{- end }}
3. **Use SCIM provisioning** from your identity provider (Azure AD, Okta, etc.) for automatic sync

### Identity Federation

If your Databricks account uses [identity federation](https://docs.databricks.com/aws/en/admin/users-groups/) with SCIM provisioning from your identity provider (IdP), groups are synced to the Databricks account and can then be assigned to workspaces. This ensures consistent group names across workspaces and automatic membership updates.
{{- end }}

